 DemoNuGridClickBug connected;F;values;cellTypes
 EWC.CONNECTEDтЖРconnected
 тОХPWтЖР1000

тНЭ Reported behavior: clicking a NuGrid cell shows the value 0 or blank in
тНЭ the embedded input, then clicking out shows the cell's original value
тНЭ correctly. Each grid below isolates one variable so we can compare the
тНЭ click-time embedded value against the static (deselected) value.

 FтЖР'F1'
 F eWC'Form' 'NuGrid Click Bug Repro'(50 50)(700 1100)('Coord' 'Pixel')

тНЭ тФАтФАтФА Grid A: baseline (matches DemoNuGrid pattern, expected to work) тФАтФАтФА
 (F,'.LA')eWC'Label' 'A: baseline'(20 20)(20 250)
 (F,'.GA')eWC'NuGrid'('Posn'(45 20))('Size'(160 320))('CellWidths'(120 100 100))('CurCell'(1 1))
 valuesAтЖР3 3тН┤'Alpha' 10 'X' 'Beta' 20 'Y' 'Gamma' 30 'Z'
 (F,'.GA')eWS('Values' valuesA)('CellTypes'(3 3тН┤1 2 3))
 (F,'.GA.E1')eWC'Edit'
 (F,'.GA.E2')eWC'Edit'('FieldType' 'Numeric')
 (F,'.GA.E3')eWC'Edit'
 (F,'.GA')eWS'Input'((F,'.GA.E1')(F,'.GA.E2')(F,'.GA.E3'))

тНЭ тФАтФАтФА Grid B: Edit templates have their own Value/Text defined тФАтФАтФА
тНЭ Hypothesis: the template's Properties.Value/Text shadows cellValue. If
тНЭ this triggers the bug, row 2 col 2 should show 0 (template default), not
тНЭ 20 (the actual cell value). Confirmed: this does NOT reproduce the bug.
 (F,'.LB')eWC'Label' 'B: templates have own Value/Text defaults'(20 360)(20 320)
 (F,'.GB')eWC'NuGrid'('Posn'(45 360))('Size'(160 320))('CellWidths'(120 100 100))('CurCell'(1 1))
 valuesBтЖР3 3тН┤'Alpha' 10 'X' 'Beta' 20 'Y' 'Gamma' 30 'Z'
 (F,'.GB')eWS('Values' valuesB)('CellTypes'(3 3тН┤1 2 3))
 (F,'.GB.E1')eWC'Edit' 'TEMPLATE-TEXT'
 (F,'.GB.E2')eWC'Edit'('FieldType' 'Numeric')('Value' 0)
 (F,'.GB.E3')eWC'Edit' ''
 (F,'.GB')eWS'Input'((F,'.GB.E1')(F,'.GB.E2')(F,'.GB.E3'))

тНЭ тФАтФАтФА Grid C: Values where rows are flat char vectors тФАтФАтФА
тНЭ Different bug, captured here for completeness: NuGrid's row iterator
тНЭ checks Array.isArray(row); a string row falls into the else-branch and
тНЭ renders as ONE cell containing the whole string ("XYZ"), not per-char.
тНЭ This is the inverse of the click-bug тАФ neither click nor blur shows the
тНЭ expected per-cell values because the cells don't exist as separate <td>s.
 (F,'.LC')eWC'Label' 'C: flat char rows (each row тЖТ 1 cell)'(220 20)(20 320)
 (F,'.GC')eWC'NuGrid'('Posn'(245 20))('Size'(160 320))('CellWidths'(80 80 80))('CurCell'(1 1))
 valuesCтЖР3 3тН┤'X' 'Y' 'Z' 'a' 'b' 'c' '1' '2' '3'
 (F,'.GC')eWS('Values' valuesC)('CellTypes'(3 3тН┤1 1 1))
 (F,'.GC.E1')eWC'Edit'
 (F,'.GC')eWS'Input'(,тКВF,'.GC.E1')

тНЭ тФАтФАтФА Grid D: cellType 2 (Numeric Edit) bound to text values тФАтФАтФА
тНЭ Hypothesis: a CellTypes/Input/value-shape mismatch causes NumericFormat
тНЭ to receive a non-numeric and render as blank/0. Click cell (1,1) which
тНЭ contains 'Alpha' but is bound to a Numeric Edit тАФ embedded input should
тНЭ show 0 or blank while the static cell shows 'Alpha'.
 (F,'.LD')eWC'Label' 'D: text values тЖТ Numeric Edit (BUG)'(220 360)(20 320)
 (F,'.GD')eWC'NuGrid'('Posn'(245 360))('Size'(160 320))('CellWidths'(120 100 100))('CurCell'(1 1))
 valuesDтЖР3 3тН┤'Alpha' 10 'X' 'Beta' 20 'Y' 'Gamma' 30 'Z'
 (F,'.GD')eWS('Values' valuesD)('CellTypes'(3 3тН┤2 2 2))    тНЭ EVERY column тЖТ Numeric Edit
 (F,'.GD.E1')eWC'Edit'
 (F,'.GD.E2')eWC'Edit'('FieldType' 'Numeric')
 (F,'.GD')eWS'Input'((F,'.GD.E1')(F,'.GD.E2'))

тНЭ тФАтФАтФА Grid E: numeric values wrapped per-cell (server-side ,┬и on Values) тФАтФАтФА
тНЭ Hypothesis: if the customer applies ,┬и to numeric Values defensively
тНЭ (mirroring the Items convention), each numeric becomes a 1-element
тНЭ vector. JSON: [[42]] instead of [[42,...]]. NumericFormat then receives
тНЭ an array and may render blank/0 while the static formatNumber path
тНЭ accidentally coerces via parseFloat([42]) тЖТ 42.
 (F,'.LE')eWC'Label' 'E: per-cell ,┬и wraps numerics'(420 20)(20 320)
 (F,'.GE')eWC'NuGrid'('Posn'(445 20))('Size'(160 320))('CellWidths'(120 100 100))('CurCell'(1 1))
 valuesEтЖР,┬и3 3тН┤'Alpha' 10 'X' 'Beta' 20 'Y' 'Gamma' 30 'Z'
 (F,'.GE')eWS('Values' valuesE)('CellTypes'(3 3тН┤1 2 3))
 (F,'.GE.E1')eWC'Edit'
 (F,'.GE.E2')eWC'Edit'('FieldType' 'Numeric')
 (F,'.GE.E3')eWC'Edit'
 (F,'.GE')eWS'Input'((F,'.GE.E1')(F,'.GE.E2')(F,'.GE.E3'))
